I removed this from my gen 4. Has had roughly 70 rounds fired through it. It does have the dot in the pentagon so it is the stronger barrel. Would be a good upgrade for an older Glock 20 or in "theory" can be used to convert a Glock 21 to shoot 10mm. See foot note. Will not work in a Glock 29 or 30. Locking lugs are not compatible.  

http://glocktalk.com/forums/showpost.php?p=16838171&postcount=2

A Glock 20 10mm factory barrel actually will function in a G21/G21SF slide and maintain good accuracy. This has been clearly proven in live-fire testing, the results of which are available in multiple cases, for example, Post #79 of the Glock Talk thread titled "Glock 21 conversion to Glock 20?" posted in the General Glocking Forum (Update: the thread has been retired). The O.D. of a G21 and G20 barrel are identical and the barrel lugs are compatible. The same holds true for an aftermarket G20 replacement barrel in the G21 slide (aftermarket G20 barrels from Bar-Sto, KKM Precision, StormLake, Lone Wolf, EFK Fire Dragon and others). While a G20 barrel is a good fit in the critical dimensions, the 10mm barrel chamber hood is narrower than the 45ACP barrel hood by slightly more than .050 inch. The dimensions of a 45-10mm conversion barrel are identical to a G20 10mm factory or aftermarket replacement barrel except that the barrel hood of the conversion barrel is made .050" wider to better fit the 45ACP pistol breechface.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Build your own BILLET AR-15: 80 percent lower receiver
postcontent:
This is a BILLET 80% Lower receiver. According to the ATF and the laws- This is not a firearm. This is an aluminum paperweight. With the correct tools and knowledge, you can complete this lower and make it into a lower receiver for an AR-15 style of rifle or pistol, completely legal. These are already de-burred and tumbled and ready to go! Requires machining out the trigger pocket and drilling the safety selector, trigger & hammer pin holes. Features the no roll pin design.


One advantage to completing this is being able to legally leave it blank or install your own marking on it. 

This is NOT your typical forged lower. This is billet- meaning it starts as a single block of aluminum and material is removed until it is in it's current state.  If you want to save money, there is a good seller on here that has $50 forged lowers. Many of the very top brands utilize billet lowers, like: Nemo, Noveske, Black Rain, Mega, etc. I just like the unique look and feel of the billet, and I just equate it to your top brands. That may not be accurate, just my thoughts. 

No bill of sale necessary, yes these can be shipped as they are just blocks of aluminum currently.

$110 for one and the price goes down if you want multiple. This is the cheapest you will find a billet 80 that is completely in spec like this one.

Here is a video on completing this into a lower as well as several photos:

http://gunnyboy.com/post_list.php?uid=3179&post=91378b331327b40e564390c43cd6b2be

title: For Sale:  Firearm resources.

Here are a few great resources I've discovered. Maybe they can help you out, too.

Genitron.com
A very comprehensive list of handguns, with many searchable specifications. On occasion, the "used" price seems a bit off, but a good site for information.

Gunbot.net
Searches the web for the best ammo prices around. Updates every few hours or so. Find what you want, price ammo.

And finally...
Google.com
Don't buy a gun without looking it up yourself.
